@node History "mFinger À History"
@{u}Version history@{uu}
mFinger 1.0 (27.11.96)
 À First release to AmiNet.

mFinger 1.1 (17.1.97)
 À Two OS 3.x functions were being called even under OS 2.x. Oops.
 À Added support for extended fingering which may or may not prompt the
   finger server to send more detailed information about the user being
   fingered. The extended fingering is enabled by checking a new menuitem
   in the Settings menu.  The default is off, and it can be enabled at
   startup by setting the tooltype EXTENDEDQUERY=YES in the icon.
   (Suggested by Tony Leneis)
 À Implemented support for T/TCP (transaction TCP) when running Miami 1.8.3
   or higher as TCP/IP stack.  Sending the finger request via T/TCP requires
   fewer packets than ordinary TCP and is thus faster.
 À Lots of new translations included.
 À This version was uploaded to aminet, but never appeared for some reason,
   and I didn't reupload it because I became aware of a couple of bugs.
   Various things delayed the next release until now..

mFinger 1.2 (5.5.97)
 ÀáFingering a host by typing "host" and not "@host" didn't work with
   "Extended query" enabled.
 ÀáToggling the "Extended query" menuitem only worked if you had MagicMenu
   installed (like me) and then only if you used the mouse and not the
   shortcut.  MagicMenu was more forgiving than Intuition about a forgotten
   flag.
   (Shaun Downend)
 ÀáAdded menuitems for saving and printing finger output.
 À Included a sample mFinger.addresses file with some interesting addresses
   collected by Andreas Grundler. Thanks Andreas!
 À Included a new version of NList.mcc which is compatible with OS 2.x (V37).
   Sorry, if you tried mFinger on 2.x previously, I guess it crashed. :)
@endnode

